      <exercise number="12.6.3">
        <p>
          <m>x^2 + 3y^2 + 9z^2 = 1</m>
        </p>

        <solution>
          <p>
            We rewrite the equation as follows: 
            <md>
              \lp \dfrac{x}{1} \rp^2 + \lp \dfrac{y}{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \rp^2 + \lp \dfrac{z^2}{\frac{1}{3}} \rp^2 = 1
            </md>
            This equation defines an ellipse. 
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>

      <exercise number="12.6.7">
        <p>
          <m>x^2 + y^2 = 4 - 4z^2</m>
        </p>

        <solution>
          <p>
            We rewrite the equation as follows: 
            <md>
              \lp \dfrac{x}{2} \rp^2 + \lp \dfrac{y}{2} \rp^2 + \lp \dfrac{z}{1} \rp^2 = 1
            </md>
            This equation defines an ellipse.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
    </exercisegroup>

